      "author": "jshph",
      "description": "Summary of changes:\r\n- Added a new plugin `copyToPluginsPlugin()` to `esbuild.config.mjs` for copying files to the plugins directory after build.\r\n- Added import statement for `copyToPlugins` function from `./scripts/copy-to-plugins.mjs` in `esbuild.config.mjs`.\r\n- Updated `plugins` array in `esbuild.config.mjs` to include `copyToPluginsPlugin()`.\r\n- Incremented version in `manifest.json` from `0.2.9` to `0.3.1`.\r\n- Modified `package.json` to introduce several new scripts:\r\n  - `preinstall`: Runs `./scripts/check-prod.js`.\r\n  - `postinstall`: Combines checking production environment and conditionally links `enzyme-core` if not in production.\r\n  - `prebuild` and `postbuild`: Execute `scripts/remove-links.js`.\r\n  - Changed `version` script to use `scripts/bump-version.js` and included `git add manifest.json versions.json`.\r\n- Changed the way `enzyme-core` is referenced in `package.json`, moving from a direct Git URL to a GitHub shorthand syntax.\r\n- Updated `pnpm-lock.yaml`:\r\n  - Changed references to `enzyme-core` to reflect the new GitHub commitment.\r\n  - Updated dependency resolutions and IDs following the `enzyme-core` reference update.\r\n  - Updated the Obsidian API dependency with a new commit hash.\r\n- Added a new script `copy-to-plugins.mjs` under `scripts` directory for copying specific files to the Obsidian plugins directory, which includes logic for defining source and destination paths, and executing the copy operation.",
      "draft": false,
      "name": "0.3.1",
      "prerelease": false,
      "publishedAt": "2024-09-04T06:56:27Z",
